    "introduction": "Giovanni Troilo is a director and photographer who works in film, television, and print media. His work has appeared in publications such as Newsweek, Der Spiegel, la Repubblica, GQ, Wired, and Wallpaper. In 2011, he directed his first feature film Fan Pio, and from 2012 to 2015 he also made a series of documentaries about Italy’s leading photographers for Sky Arte. His project La Ville Noire – The Dark Heart of Europe won a prize at the Sony World Photography Awards. His documentaries include Frida – viva la vida, Le Ninfee di Monet, Vesuvio, Power of Rome, Borromini e Bernini (winner of a Silver Ribbon), and the two-part documentary Mauro Rostagno. L’uomo che voleva cambiare il mondo, co-directed with author Roberto Saviano. Since 2015, Troilo has been the artistic director or PhEST, the international festival of photography and visual arts in Monopoli. He is currently working on his second feature film, set in Belgium.",
